import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Penicillin'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin effectiveness against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', y='Streptomycin', hue='Bacteria', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Penicillin and Streptomycin effectiveness against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Penicillin', 'Streptomycin', 'Neomycin', 'Gram_Staining']]
    data = pd.melt(data, id_vars=['Gram_Staining'], var_name='Antibiotic', value_name='Effectiveness')
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='Antibiotic', y='Effectiveness', hue='Gram_Staining', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Gram Staining and effectiveness of antibiotics against the bacteria?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
